I don't like this one, but users asked for it:

If you want to "polute" your code, you can use the @org.ucdetector.util.UsedBy
annotation located inside ucdetector-annotations.jar which is inside org.ucdetector.xxx.jar.
/**
 * Class is only used by reflection.
 * Add a @SuppressWarnings("ucd") annotation.
 * This class/method/field will be ignored by UCDetector.
 */
@UsedBy("reflection")
public class BeanExample {


